    {
      "id": "bae4986d_b794ef73",
      "file_path": "components/pm-subscription-handler/pmsh_service/mod/network_function.py",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 122,
      "message": "Not sure if if statements are the way to go, probably simpler, but I guess another way to go about it without them would be to introduce something along the lines, but this is just purely an idea (probably need some name refactoring in the code):\n\n        match = True\n        if orchestration_status != 'Active':\n            return False\n\n        check_for_name = self.nf_names and self.regex_matcher.search(nf_name) is None\n        check_for_invariant_id = self.invariant_uuids and not len([entityid for entityid in self.invariant_uuids\n                                             if entityid == invariant_uuid]) > 0\n        check_for_uuids = self.uuids and not len([entityid for entityid in self.uuids if entityid == uuid]) > 0\n\n        checks = [check_for_name or check_for_invariant_id or check_for_uuids]\n\n        if any(checks):\n            match = False\n\n        return match\n\nAlso a bit confused about this maybe its just hard for me alone to follow this, but as long as it works as intended I've no issues -  'and not len([entityid for entityid in self.invariant_uuids if entityid == invariant_uuid]) > 0'",
      "author": {
